  We describe how to transform an asymmetric traveling salesman problem into a symmetric one at the cost of almost doubled problem size. Use and consequences are discussed shortly. Keywords Traveling salesman problem [1] E. Balas, N. Christofides A restricted Lagrangean approach to the traveling salesman problem Math. Programming, 21 (1981), pp. 19–46 [2] M.S. Bazaraa, J.J. Goode The traveling salesman problem: A duality approach Math. Programming, 13 (1977), pp. 221–237 [3] M. Held, R.M. Karp The traveling-salesman problem and minimum spinning trees Math. Programming, 1 (1971), pp. 6–26 [4] R.M. Karp Reducibility among combinatorial problems R.E. Miller, J.W. Thatcher (Eds.), Complexity of Computer Computations (1972) New York [5] S. Lin Computer solutions of the traveling salesman problem Bell Syst. Techn. J., 44 (1965), pp. 2245–2269 [6] A. Volgenant, R. Jonker The symmetric traveling salesman problem and edge exchanges in minimal 1-trees European J. Oper. Res., 12 (1983), pp. 394–403 Copyright © 1983 Published by Elsevier B.V.